# Adding a New Data Source

## Source of Truth

All data sources are backed by `github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3`, vendored at
`vendor/github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3/zscaler/zia/services/<package>/`.
**The SDK defines available fields and getter functions.** Always start by reading
the SDK return types and Get/GetByName/GetAll functions.

If the SDK needs updating: `go get github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3@latest && go mod vendor`

## Steps

1. **Check the SDK**: Read the return types and getter functions in `vendor/github.com/zscaler/zscaler-sdk-go/v3/zscaler/zia/services/<package>/`
2. **Create** `provider/<datasource_name>.go` with Args, Result, Function structs mapping to SDK types
3. **Implement** `Invoke(ctx, infer.FunctionRequest[Args]) (infer.FunctionResponse[Result], error)` calling SDK getters
3. **Add Annotate()** methods (all pointer receivers):
   - Function: describe purpose
   - Args: describe each lookup field
   - Result: describe each output field
4. **Register** in `provider/provider.go` under `WithFunctions()` (pass pointer: `&GetFoo{}`)
5. **Build**: `make provider && make generate_schema`

## Template

```go
type GetFooArgs struct {
    Id   *int    `pulumi:"resourceId,optional"`
    Name *string `pulumi:"name,optional"`
}

type GetFooResult struct {
    Id   int    `pulumi:"resourceId"`
    Name string `pulumi:"name"`
}

type GetFoo struct{}

func (f *GetFoo) Annotate(a infer.Annotator) {
    a.Describe(f, "Use this data source to look up a Foo by ID or name.")
}

func (a *GetFooArgs) Annotate(ann infer.Annotator) {
    ann.Describe(&a.Id, "The ID of the Foo to look up.")
    ann.Describe(&a.Name, "The name of the Foo to look up.")
}

func (r *GetFooResult) Annotate(a infer.Annotator) {
    a.Describe(&r.Id, "The ID of the Foo.")
    a.Describe(&r.Name, "The name of the Foo.")
}

func (*GetFoo) Invoke(ctx context.Context, req infer.FunctionRequest[GetFooArgs]) (infer.FunctionResponse[GetFooResult], error) {
    cfg := infer.GetConfig[Config](ctx)
    if cfg.Client() == nil {
        return infer.FunctionResponse[GetFooResult]{}, fmt.Errorf("ZIA provider not configured")
    }
    svc := cfg.Client().Service
    // ... lookup logic ...
}
```

## Key Differences from Resources

- Functions use `infer.Function(&GetFoo{})` (pointer, not value)
- All Annotate methods use pointer receivers
- No CRUD — only `Invoke`
- No State struct — use Result struct
